Product Name: APC Smart-UPS On-Line, 10kVA/10kW, Tower, 208V, 6x C13+4x C19 IEC outlets, Network Card+SmartSlot, Extended runtime, W/O rail kit
Short description:
Replacement battery (3) is available
 
 10kVA/10kW double-conversion on-line pure sine wave tower UPS
 
 Ideal for servers, storage, voice/data networks, medical labs, and light industrial applications
 
 Rack/Tower convertible (rail kit SRTRK2 or SRTRK3 sold separately)
 
 1-Year Secure Network Management Card subscription included
 
 Add up to 10 external battery packs (SRT192BP2) for extended runtime
Product Description: This APC Smart-UPS is designed for IT professionals or network administrators to maintain business uptime and continuity. This 10kVA on-line tower UPS provides pure sine wave power and extended runtime to support critical electronics during power disruptions. It comes with hard wire 3-wire (2P+E) input, 6x IEC 320 C13 and 4x IEC 320 C19 outlets, and 3x IEC jumper cables. The UPS has an embedded Network Management Card for UPS network-based monitoring and management. The UPS comes with PowerChute Network Shutdown that provides graceful shutdown of physical servers, virtual machines, and HCI clusters. It has an additional SmartSlot for optional accessory card such as Dry Contact I/O card. The UPS can connect to EcoStruxure IT or third-party centralized management platforms. The UPS has a 3-year warranty, and the built-in lead-acid battery has a 2-year warranty. The UPS is compatible with SRTRK2 (4-post) and SRTRK3 (2-post) rail kits sold separately.

Product Name: APC Smart-UPS, Line Interactive, 700VA, Tower, 120V, 8x NEMA 5-15R outlets, SmartSlot, Auto Sense Voltage 120V/230V, AVR, LCD
Short description:
700VA/450W line interactive pure sine wave tower UPS
 
 Ideal for servers, storage, network closets, business VoIP & desktops, retail POS
 
 Automatic Voltage Regulation helps correct utility voltage
 
 Graceful shutdown using serial or USB cables via PowerChute Business Edition
Product Description: This APC Smart-UPS is designed for IT professionals or network administrators to maintain business uptime and continuity. The 700VA line interactive tower UPS provides pure sine wave power to support critical electronics during power disruptions. It comes with NEMA 5-15P input and 8 NEMA 5-15R outlets. It has a SmartSlot for optional Network Management Card that enables graceful shutdown of physical servers, virtual machines & HCI Clusters via PowerChute Network Shutdown. It has a SmartSlot for optional Network Management Card that enables graceful shutdown of physical servers, virtual machines & HCI Clusters via PowerChute Network Shutdown. The UPS can connect to EcoStruxure IT or third-party centralized management platforms. It provides surge protection against lightning strikes, power sags, brownouts and surges. The SMT UPS has a 3-year warranty, and the built-in lead-acid battery has a 2-year warranty. It is compatible with a dedicated user-replaceable battery, and the APC replacement battery cartridge helps restore UPS performance to the original specifications.

Product Name: APC Netshelter Rack Automatic Transfer Switch, 1U, 10A, 230V, C14 IN, 12 C13 OUT, 50/60Hz
Product Description: APC NetShelter Rack Automatic Transfer Switch (ATS) AP4421A is the Fifth-Generation range of high availability switches offering greater control of your IT equipment from Cloud to Edge. With Industry leading reliability, agility, and manageability the APC NetShelter Rack ATS provides redundant power to single-corded equipment loads in the IT rack. AP4421A is single phase 1U Rack ATS with 10A rated current, 230V rated voltage and 2000VA load capacity. It comes with 2 IEC C14 inlet and 12 IEC C13 outlet sockets. This has been upgraded with APC NMC3 and various technical advancements for network port sharing, environmental monitoring and enhanced security. It has 2-years of standard warranty and 5-years of extended warranty for peace of mind and use for years to come. Users can access and configure Rack ATS through secure Web UI, SNMP, CLI and are fully compatible with EcoStruxure IT.

Product Description: APC NetShelter Rack Automatic Transfer Switch (ATS) AP4430A is the Fifth-Generation range of high availability switches offering greater control of your IT equipment from Cloud to Edge. With Industry leading reliability, agility, and manageability the APC NetShelter Rack ATS provides redundant power to single-corded equipment loads in the IT rack. AP4430A is single phase 1U Rack ATS with 20A rated current, 200V/208V rated voltage and 3300VA load capacity. For North America region, the Regulatory Derated Input Current is 16A. It comes with 2 NEMA L6-20P inlet and 8 IEC C13, 1 IEC C19 outlet sockets. This has been upgraded with APC NMC3 and various technical advancements for network port sharing, environmental monitoring and enhanced security. It has 2-years of standard warranty and 5-years of extended warranty for peace of mind and use for years to come. Users can access and configure Rack ATS through secure Web UI, SNMP, CLI and are fully compatible with EcoStruxure IT.

Product Name: APC NetShelter Rack PDU, Switched, 0U, 5.0kW 200V and 208V 30A, (21) C13/C15 and (3) C19/C21 outlets
Short description:
Ideal for colocation, large data centers or distributed IT sites
 
 Remote management of rack PDUs for efficient time-saving
 
 Plan capacity and balance loads with +/- 1% metering accuracy (amps, volts, kW, kWh)
 
 Gigabit ethernet connectivity
 
 Real-time remote monitoring of connected load through EcoStruxureTM IT and other platforms
Product Description: The APC Switched Rack PDU distributes reliable power within a rack through a single input and multiple output receptacles The APDU9941 offers advanced load management combined with remote on/off switching control of individual outlets for power cycling, delayed power sequencing, and outlet use management The 0U PDU includes a NEMA L6-30P input plug with 3 05m (10 ft) cord, (21) IEC 60320 C13/C15 and (3) IEC 60320 C19/C21 hybrid outlet receptacles The hybrid outlets allow 60Â°C operating temperature at full load, are compatible with standard C14 and C20 power cords, and are future-proofed for new C16 and C21 power cords required for higher temperature rated devices The Network Management Card provides enhanced cybersecurity with secured interfaces and modified password policy The rack PDU integrates with EcoStruxure IT through Network Management Card and can be accessed, configured, and managed remotely via Web, SNMP and Command Line Interface Color user-interactive LCD interface details current, real power, voltage, and energy measurements for local user access The outlet level control allows power on/off functionality for power recycling/reboot of remote equipment and restricts unauthorized use of individual outlets The Switched Rack PDU includes a temperature/humidity sensor port, locking IEC outlets when used with locking power cords, low-profile circuit breakers and USB port for local Firmware updates The rack PDU supports daisy-chain of up to 32 PDUs on a single IP address, thereby reducing networking cost The rack PDU comes with a standard three-year warranty
